Or in IronPython:<p><pre><code>  currentNetTypes = sorted(
  		sum(
  			list(asm.getExportedTypes())
  			for asm in System.AppDomain.CurrentDomain.GetAssemblies()
  			if 'Version=4.0.0.0' in asm.FullName), 
  		lambda a, b: cmp(len(a.Name), len(b.Name))
  	)
</code></pre>
Clean, but I love how the <i>|></i> operator in F# serves to flatten code like this.
